>diplomacy (including all the subsequent Internomic proposals). The
>existence of "dissenters", "pacifists" or even "traitors" is also an
>integral part of the politics of conflict - let's play that out and
>enjoy it!

Hear! Hear!  But sometimes it *is* hard not to get so caught up in things that
we take it too seriously (or sometimes too personally).  Beware of causing
narcissistic injuries! (That's what Rishonomic did to Agora when they called us
"boring".) 8)  Morendil's actions *did* cause a lot of interesting events and e
took a lot of criticism for it.  I'm glad e seems to have taken it in stride
and I hope we continue to get out of these little spats without any blood on
the floor.  8)

>I think in Agora I'll have to choose a middle way - I'll try to be
>myself as far as manners and procedures are concerned, but I will
>behave just as if I was playing any other _game_ face to face, so
>things that are allowed within the rules, including warfare (and
>treason!) are ok as long as they contribute to the general enjoyment
>of the game and don't completely spoil the game for others.

Excellent choice. 8)

-- Crito (who also tends to make long posts).

P.S.  I've gotten used to this spivak pronoun stuff in a way, but I still find
myself mentally translating them whenever I read them (kind of a pain). 
Personally, I think using third person plural to refer to singular persons of
indeterminate sex is perfectly fine in English.  After all we have the
precedent of using the plural form to refer to both singular and plural in the
second person.


