"Klaus" == Klaus Herrmanns NB6 25 (3751) <klaush@spinup.tp3.ruhr-uni-bochum.de> writes:

Klaus> On the other hand, I think that some pressure on the political
Klaus> decision making (which certainly is a focus of a Nomic game)
Klaus> could be produced in much simpler ways using the structures
Klaus> that already exist. Ignoring the technical problems around
Klaus> "Restore Game Balance" there is such a huge number of VTs and
Klaus> P-notes around that I would really like to ask you (this is an
Klaus> honest question, not a rhetorical one, so I'd appreciate
Klaus> getting some answers!): did you ever feel that you did not have
Klaus> enough VTs or P-notes to do things you wanted to do? 

We have not been successful at creating scarcity yet, but I think it's
on the way. 

Klaus> I don't mean just the general habit of being present instead of
Klaus> voting on not-so-hot issues - did you ever face a "tough"
Klaus> decision whether to use a VT or P-note or not? Or is one of the
Klaus> lessons to learn here (and a very interesting one it would be!)
Klaus> that in a democracy it is very hard to adopt proposals that
Klaus> make life harder for everyone?

Generally, yes.  You have to either sneak them past people or make a
compelling reason why the added burden serves some greater good.

Klaus> What would you think about making the VTs a more scarce
Klaus> currency, like for example (rough sketch, not even
Klaus> protoproposal level, just to give you the idea):

Klaus> Limit the overall number of VTs to five times the number of
Klaus> players (ouch - but that's the point!). If the bank is required
Klaus> to give out VTs it doesn't have (by Rule 1684 or whatever else)
Klaus> it collects a tax from all players, either a flat tax (everyone
Klaus> pays 1 Nth of the required amount, where N is the number of
Klaus> active players) or a percentage of the VTs in eir treasury.

Interesting concept.  Note that our present concept of currencies
effectively makes the Bank bottomless, because the Bank can go
indefinitely negative without substantial consequence.  (This is
untrue under the system I propose in the Pragmatic Currencies Proposal
recently Promoted, by the way; your suggestion is more relevant under
that conceptualization.)

Klaus> This would make spending VTs harder, non-voting penalties
Klaus> harsher etc - you must admit that even after a balance restore
Klaus> transfers of 0.5 VTs don't really make a difference if you have
Klaus> 20 of them to vote on five proposals a week.

I want to repeal the non-voting penalty.  I also want to repeal the
general stipend.  The second is a poor effort to rectify the
unbalancing affect of the first.  There has to be a better way. 

Klaus> But it would not create more red tape, manual work etc, at
Klaus> least not as much as the bookkeeping for plots, production etc.

I'm willing to accept a reasonable amount of bookkeeping if it makes
the game more interesting.


