Crito wrote:
>>I'm not against making VTs really scarce, per se.  However, I think most of us
tend to be very wary of the possibility that it might become impossible for a
Player to vote at all (or make proposals, although some Players are content to
play without proposing).<<

Of course that is a crucial point, and I would certainly not want to
make it impossible to vote (or propose things). But I think it could
be solved within the general framework of very scarce VTs, with 
appropriate finetuning of the taxation system (like a minimum income
and/or amount of VTs in each player's treasury that can not be touched
by the tax collector). 

In Germany income tax works like that: not only the gross amount of
tax you pay depends on your gross income, but the _percentage_ of your
gross income that is your tax varies with income, as well: from zero -
no income tax at all - for people with very low income (like me :) to
a top tax rate of 50% or so.

So your point is definitly valid (and as a new player without any
regular source of Agora currencies from salaries etc I am certainly
very much concerned by this), but solving it would be part of the fun
of introducing taxation.

Kolja A.

